  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal by reason of an undersized bedroom at first floor and the kitchen being shared by more than 5 occupiers creates a poor standard of internal amenity for occupiers of the C4 HMO. The proposal is therefore contrary to polices DM D2 of the Sites and Policies Plan 2014, and policies CS 8, CS9 and CS14 within the Council's Adopted Core Strategy 2011.",
    "Reason : 2 - In the absence of a refuse and recycling enclosure/storage for the development, the proposal fails to accord with Policies SI 7 & SI 8 of the London Plan 2021,  Merton Core Strategy 2011 policies CS14 & CS17 and Policies DM D2 of the SPP 2014.",
    "Reason : 3 - In the absence of a satisfactory Air Quality Neutral Statement, the applicant has failed to demonstrate that the development is at minimum air quality neutral, thereby failing to comply with policy SI1 of the London Plan 2021",
    "Reason : 4 - The proposal fails to include any information relating to sustainable drainage and therefore the proposed development has failed to meet the objectives of policies SI 2 and SI 5 of the London Plan 2021 and policy CS15 of Merton Core Planning Strategy (2011)",
    "Reason : 5 - INFORMATIVE \r\n\r\nNote to Applicant - Refused Schemes \r\n\r\nIn accordance with paragraph 38 of the National Planning Policy Framework, London Borough of Merton (LBM) takes a positive and proactive approach to the delivery of sustainable development, by: \r\n1. Providing a formal pre-application advice service, details to be found on Planning pre-application advice service on LBM�s website \r\n2. Providing written policies and guidance, which is available to view on LBM�s website. \r\n3. Where appropriate, negotiating amendments to secure a positive decision. \r\n4. Determining applications in a timely manner including providing a fast track service, details to be found on Get a quicker planning decision on LBM�s website.\r\nIn this instance: \r\nThe applicants did not seek formal pre-application advice, and the scheme was found to be contrary to policy and guidance, and subsequently refused. The Council recomments the applicant/agent to enter into formal pre-application discussions to advise the applicant/agent of relevant policy and guidance; and where possible assist in the preparation of a new planning permission. \r\n"
  ],
